01:29.524 --> 01:33.441
♪ I'LL BE READY
[I'LL BE READY] ♪

01:33.571 --> 01:37.445
♪ WHENEVER YOU FEAR
[NO DON'T YOU FEAR] ♪

01:37.575 --> 01:40.056
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:40.839 --> 01:43.886
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:44.016 --> 01:46.280
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:01.425 --> 02:03.253
-[GENTLE MUSIC]

02:51.910 --> 02:54.696
-BOB: ALL RIGHT, LET'S
HOIST HER ABOARD HERE, HUH?

02:54.826 --> 02:56.480
[LAUGHS]

02:56.611 --> 03:01.790
OOH WEE, THAT IS
A BEAUTIFUL SIGHT.

03:05.968 --> 03:07.622
[LAUGHS]

03:12.322 --> 03:14.977
JOHNNY, ME BOY,
IT LOOKS LIKE

03:15.107 --> 03:16.718
WE'RE GONNA HAVE A
GREAT DAY TODAY, HUH?

03:16.848 --> 03:19.155
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

03:28.425 --> 03:29.600
-ANYTHING?

03:29.731 --> 03:31.341
-JUST A FISHING
BOAT UP AHEAD.

03:42.613 --> 03:44.441
-BOB: GIVE ME YOUR
HAND, NICKY ME BOY.

03:46.704 --> 03:49.054
[SCREAMING]

03:56.018 --> 03:57.802
-JOHNNY! JOHNNY!

03:57.933 --> 03:59.369
JOHNNY!

03:59.500 --> 04:01.980
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

04:03.547 --> 04:06.289
-I THINK THEY'RE IN
TROUBLE, LET'S GO.

04:08.378 --> 04:09.814
-NICKY: OVER HERE!

04:10.772 --> 04:12.121
OVER HERE!

04:12.817 --> 04:15.167
JOHNNY! JOHNNY!

04:15.298 --> 04:16.517
-JOHNNY: WHOA!

04:19.214 --> 04:21.478
-[SIRENS]

04:22.914 --> 04:24.046
-NICKY: OVER HERE!

04:25.917 --> 04:26.918
OVER HERE!

04:28.311 --> 04:29.617
SAVE US!

04:31.923 --> 04:32.837
HELP!

04:39.757 --> 04:42.107
MY BROTHER FELL
OUT OF THE BOAT!

04:42.238 --> 04:44.153
I DON'T KNOW
WHERE HE IS!

04:44.284 --> 04:45.676
-APRIL, LANI,
GET THEM ON BOARD.

04:47.069 --> 04:48.331
-[MOANS]

04:49.637 --> 04:50.812
-LANI: HELP ME.
-APRIL: OKAY!

05:03.259 --> 05:05.000
NO PULSE, BEGIN CPR.

05:05.870 --> 05:09.178
-ONE, TWO,
THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

05:11.006 --> 05:13.965
ONE, TWO,
THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

05:14.096 --> 05:15.010
-COME ON.

05:15.140 --> 05:16.316
-HE'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

05:16.446 --> 05:19.144
-J.D.: ONE, TWO,
THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

05:19.275 --> 05:20.885
-[COUGHING]

05:21.016 --> 05:22.060
-[SIGHS]

05:27.457 --> 05:31.331
-OH MAN, OH MAN, I MUST'VE
AGED ANOTHER 10 YEARS.

05:32.680 --> 05:35.726
YOU FOLKS SAVED ME, YOU
SAVED ME, YOU SAVED MY BOYS.

05:36.684 --> 05:39.077
AND YOU SAVED MY
CATCH. [LAUGHS]

05:39.208 --> 05:40.122
I OWE YA.

05:40.731 --> 05:41.689
I'M CAPTAIN BOB.

05:42.254 --> 05:43.081
-J.D.

05:43.212 --> 05:44.735
THIS IS IS APRIL, LANI.

05:44.866 --> 05:46.171
-IT'S A PLEASURE
TO MEET YA ALL.

05:46.302 --> 05:47.390
-PLEASED TO MEET YOU.

05:48.348 --> 05:50.350
-[RATTLING ENGINE]

06:04.799 --> 06:05.800
-[COUGHING]

06:06.801 --> 06:07.671
-[CAR BACKFIRES]

06:11.283 --> 06:12.415
-[COUGHING]

06:28.823 --> 06:30.477
-THINK I NEED A
MECHANIC TO FIX IT.

06:30.607 --> 06:32.957
-YEAH, OR A PRIEST
TO GIVE IT LAST RITES.

06:34.698 --> 06:37.658
-PROBABLY THREW A ROD,
MAYBE CRACKED A HEAD.

06:39.616 --> 06:41.139
COULD'VE SEIZED THE ENGINE.

06:41.270 --> 06:43.272
-CODY, DO YOU EVEN KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT?

06:43.881 --> 06:45.317
-ABSOLUTELY NOT.

06:46.057 --> 06:47.711
MY DAD USED TO
SAY THOSE THINGS,

06:47.842 --> 06:49.583
I NEVER REALLY
LEARNED ABOUT CARS.

06:51.454 --> 06:54.326
-WELL I THOUGHT THAT WAS A
REQUIRED COURSE, MACHO 101.

06:54.979 --> 06:55.893
-GUESS I FLUNKED.

06:56.590 --> 06:58.026
YOU KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT CARS?

06:58.156 --> 06:59.114
-EH, SOME.

07:00.681 --> 07:01.899
-WHAT DO YOU THINK IT'S
GONNA TAKE TO FIX THIS?

07:02.900 --> 07:04.511
-HONESTLY, A MIRACLE.

07:05.294 --> 07:06.817
-SERIOUSLY, WHAT AM
I LOOKING AT HERE?

07:08.428 --> 07:09.733
-1200 BUCKS MINIMUM.

07:10.865 --> 07:11.735
-OH.

07:12.693 --> 07:13.520
IT IS A MIRACLE.

07:14.259 --> 07:15.347
-[COUGHS]

07:21.136 --> 07:22.137
-[SNEEZE]

07:22.659 --> 07:23.965
-BLESS YOU!

07:24.095 --> 07:25.793
-THANKS, I THINK
I'M GETTING A COLD.

07:37.979 --> 07:40.677
-SO, WHAT DOES CAPTAIN BOB
DO WITH ALL THOSE SEA URCHINS?

07:40.808 --> 07:43.463
-HE MUST SELL 'EM TO SUSHI
BARS OR EXPORT THEM TO JAPAN.

07:43.593 --> 07:45.247
-APRIL: WELL WHY JAPAN?

07:45.377 --> 07:47.118
-WELL THEY'RE CONSIDERED
A DELICACY IN THE FAR EAST.

07:47.249 --> 07:48.380
-WELL, WHAT PART
DO YOU EAT?

07:48.511 --> 07:49.556
I THOUGHT IT
WAS ALL SHELL.

07:50.078 --> 07:51.296
-YOU SEE, CRACK
IT OPEN LIKE AN EGG

07:51.427 --> 07:52.472
AND THEN YOU
EAT THE INSIDES.

07:52.602 --> 07:54.169
-UH, SOUNDS GROSS.

07:55.083 --> 07:57.433
-ALL I KNOW IS THEY SELL
FOR 500 DOLLARS A POUND.

07:57.564 --> 07:59.348
OH AND GET THIS, CAPTAIN BOB
SAID WE CAN DIVE WITH HIM

07:59.479 --> 08:01.045
AND WE COULD KEEP
HALF OF WHAT WE CATCH.

08:01.176 --> 08:03.395
-HAVE YOU EVER DOVE
FOR SEA URCHINS BEFORE?

08:03.526 --> 08:05.833
-NO, BUT HOW
HARD COULD IT BE?

08:08.966 --> 08:10.315
-MITCH: HEY, WHY
ARE YOU SO LATE?

08:10.446 --> 08:12.230
-CODY: OH, CAR BROKE
DOWN THIS MORNING.

08:12.361 --> 08:14.668
HAD TO WAIT FOR THE TOW TRUCK,
TOOK 'EM FOREVER TO GET HERE.

08:15.320 --> 08:16.757
-MITCH: WHAT HAPPENED?

08:16.887 --> 08:18.323
-CODY: I EITHER FROZE
A ROD OR BLEW A GASKET.

08:19.107 --> 08:20.238
I DON'T KNOW, YOU
HAVE TO ASK JORDAN.

08:20.369 --> 08:21.196
-MITCH: JORDAN?

08:21.936 --> 08:22.763
-CODY: JORDAN.

08:29.465 --> 08:30.553
-MITCH: NICE SURF, HUH?

08:30.684 --> 08:31.554
-CODY: YEAH.

08:32.467 --> 08:34.339
SO ANYWAY, NOW I HAVE
TO DECIDE WHETHER TO

08:34.470 --> 08:36.994
BUY ANOTHER CAR OR FIX
THAT PIECE OF JUNK.

08:37.517 --> 08:38.518
-THAT'S A TOUGH CALL.

08:39.169 --> 08:40.823
-NOT REALLY, I'M BROKE.

08:41.695 --> 08:43.087
HEY, WHAT ARE MY
CHANCES OF GETTING

08:43.217 --> 08:44.261
SOME EXTRA
HOURS THIS MONTH?

08:44.393 --> 08:45.960
-I DON'T KNOW,

08:46.090 --> 08:47.135
YOU HAVE TO TALK TO
LIEUTENANT WALSH ABOUT THAT.

08:48.136 --> 08:49.703
-CAN'T YOU AT LEAST PUT
IN A GOOD WORD FOR ME?

08:50.704 --> 08:51.835
-I DON'T KNOW,
SHE'S PRETTY TOUGH

08:51.966 --> 08:53.141
ABOUT CHANGING
THE SCHEDULE.

08:56.144 --> 08:59.016
-[SOFT MUSIC]

09:06.154 --> 09:07.111
-WHAT'S UP?

09:07.242 --> 09:08.025
WHAT ARE YOU LOOKING FOR?

09:09.592 --> 09:11.072
-MITCH: RIGHT ON TIME.

09:13.553 --> 09:15.250
OKAY, YOUR DAY BEGINS.

09:15.816 --> 09:18.383
HORSES ARE NOT
ALLOWED ON THE BEACH.

09:18.514 --> 09:19.602
I WANT YOU TO
GET HER NAME,

09:19.733 --> 09:21.909
ADDRESS, OCCUPATION, AND UM

09:22.736 --> 09:23.563
CITE HER.

09:24.868 --> 09:25.695
-A CITATION?

09:25.826 --> 09:27.305
-YEAH, NEW PROCEDURE.

09:29.569 --> 09:30.439
-ALL RIGHT.

09:31.919 --> 09:34.008
-[MITCH HUMMING]

09:55.769 --> 09:57.292
[LAUGHING]

09:57.422 --> 10:00.817
[WHISTLING]

10:00.948 --> 10:01.731
-CODY: 'MORNING.

10:01.862 --> 10:02.993
-HI.

10:03.124 --> 10:04.865
-LISTEN, SORRY
TO SPOIL YOUR FUN

10:04.995 --> 10:07.258
BUT HORSES AREN'T
ALLOWED ON THE BEACH.

10:07.389 --> 10:10.610
I'M GONNA HAVE TO GET YOUR
NAME, ADDRESS, OCCUPATION.

10:10.740 --> 10:13.047
-OH, WELL MY NAME'S JENNY
WADE, I'M A HORSE TRAINER.

10:13.177 --> 10:16.572
I LIVE OVER AT DECKER
CANYON, 22250, BUT I...

10:16.703 --> 10:18.226
-I HATE TO GIVE YOU
A CITATION, BUT UM...

10:18.356 --> 10:20.663
-JENNY: A CITATION?
-CODY: NEW PROCEDURE.

10:20.794 --> 10:23.057
-MY HORSE IS RECUPERATING
FROM AN OPERATION,

10:23.187 --> 10:24.493
HE NEEDS THE FOOTING
ON THE BEACH.

10:25.015 --> 10:26.756
THE ONLY LEGAL BEACH
FOR HORSES IS WHERE

10:26.887 --> 10:29.629
THE RICH AND FAMOUS LIVE AND
I DON'T QUALIFY FOR EITHER.

10:29.759 --> 10:31.021
-I KNOW, BUT I JUST...

10:31.152 --> 10:31.979
THERE'S NOTHING I
CAN DO ABOUT IT.

10:32.109 --> 10:33.371
-THAT'S OKAY CODY.

10:33.502 --> 10:35.330
HI, I'M MITCH, CAPTAIN
MITCH BUCHANNON.

10:35.460 --> 10:36.853
-HI.

10:36.984 --> 10:38.681
-I DON'T THINK WE
HAVE TO GIVE MISS UH?

10:38.812 --> 10:41.597
-JENNY: WADE.
-MISS WADE A CITATION.

10:41.728 --> 10:43.773
WE SHOULD JUST GIVE HER A
WARNING, DON'T YOU THINK?

10:46.471 --> 10:48.517
-OBEY ALL THE RULES AND
YOU MISS ALL THE FUN.

10:49.300 --> 10:50.084
-KATHARINE HEPBURN.

10:50.214 --> 10:51.346
-THAT'S RIGHT.

10:52.434 --> 10:53.348
AND THANKS.

10:57.352 --> 10:58.222
-HAVE A NICE DAY.

10:59.180 --> 11:00.137
-JENNY: THANKS, I WILL.

11:01.878 --> 11:02.749
-[MITCH SIGHS]

11:03.358 --> 11:05.882
-UH, UH, UH,
NOT SO FAST.

11:07.362 --> 11:09.277
I SHOULD'VE KNOWN WHEN YOU
INSISTED ON GIVING ME A RIDE

11:09.407 --> 11:11.018
TO MY TOWER THIS MORNING
THAT SOMETHING WAS GOING ON.

11:11.583 --> 11:12.367
YOU SET ME UP.

11:12.497 --> 11:13.324
-ME?

11:13.455 --> 11:14.848
[LAUGHING]

11:15.544 --> 11:16.893
ALL RIGHT, I DID
SET YOU UP.

11:17.024 --> 11:19.853
SHE'S BEEN RIDING ON
THE BEACH EVERY MORNING

11:19.983 --> 11:21.376
FOR THE LAST FIVE
DAYS AT THE SAME TIME.

11:21.506 --> 11:22.769
I JUST HAD TO
MEET HER, MAN.

11:22.899 --> 11:24.118
-AND MAKE AN IMPRESSION.

11:24.248 --> 11:25.293
-WELL I HOPE SO.

11:26.207 --> 11:27.687
-SO WHAT'S YOUR
NEXT MOVE, CASANOVA?

11:27.817 --> 11:30.559
-WELL THAT'S FOR ME TO
KNOW, AND YOU TO ENVY.

11:30.690 --> 11:31.691
[LAUGHS]

11:32.474 --> 11:34.041
-RIDING LESSONS?

11:35.085 --> 11:36.130
-YEAH.

11:36.652 --> 11:38.349
BUGGED ME TO DEATH ABOUT
TAKING RIDING LESSONS.

11:38.480 --> 11:39.960
-WHEN I WAS
NINE YEARS OLD.

11:40.090 --> 11:42.266
-WELL, BETTER LATE
THAN NEVER I ALWAYS SAY.

11:42.397 --> 11:43.746
-NO, WHAT YOU ALWAYS SAY

11:43.877 --> 11:45.095
IS BE HONEST WITH
YOURSELF AND OTHERS.

11:45.226 --> 11:46.314
SO COME ON, GIVE IT UP.

11:46.444 --> 11:47.837
-NO, IT'S NO BIG DEAL.

11:47.968 --> 11:49.752
IT'S JUST THAT I KNOW
HOW MUCH YOU WANT

11:49.883 --> 11:52.015
TO TAKE RIDING LESSONS AND I
MET THIS REALLY GREAT TEACHER.

11:52.146 --> 11:54.017
-WHO'S THE GUY THAT'S
GONNA BE TEACHING ME?

11:54.148 --> 11:57.107
-UM, IT'S NOT A
GUY, IT'S A GIRL.

11:58.979 --> 12:01.198
AND, YOU'LL LOVE HER,
SHE IS TOTALLY AWESOME.

12:03.505 --> 12:05.725
OH! [GRUNTS]

12:05.855 --> 12:08.205
EMPTY, MILK, PUT
MILK ON THE LIST.

12:11.078 --> 12:13.341
-SO, HOW AWESOME IS SHE?

12:13.471 --> 12:15.778
AND WHO EXACTLY IS
IT THAT'LL LOVE HER?

12:16.692 --> 12:19.216
-HOBIE, SHE IS SO
AWESOME THAT I CANNOT

12:19.347 --> 12:22.437
GET ON A HORSE IN FRONT OF
HER, I'LL LOOK LIKE A GEEK.

12:22.567 --> 12:23.960
-OH, BUT IT'S OKAY FOR
ME TO LOOK LIKE A GEEK?

12:24.613 --> 12:25.353
-YEAH.

12:25.483 --> 12:26.484
-THANKS.

12:27.747 --> 12:28.704
THAT AWESOME HUH?

12:28.835 --> 12:30.271
-THAT AWESOME.

12:31.185 --> 12:33.970
-THEN YOU KNOW WHAT I ALWAYS
SAY, WHAT ARE SONS FOR, RIGHT?

12:34.536 --> 12:36.973
IF NOT TO HELP THEIR
OLD MAN GET A DATE.

12:48.028 --> 12:49.681
-CODY: SEA URCHINS?

12:49.812 --> 12:50.944
-COME ON, DO YOU KNOW HOW
MUCH MONEY WE COULD MAKE?

12:51.074 --> 12:52.293
-DO YOU KNOW HOW
DANGEROUS THAT IS?

12:52.423 --> 12:53.642
IT'S NOT LIKE
DIGGING FOR CLAMS.

12:54.208 --> 12:56.297
IN HAWAII I KNEW SOMEONE
WHO STEPPED ON A SEA URCHIN,

12:56.427 --> 12:57.864
HAD THE SPINES GET
STUCK IN HIS FOOT

12:57.994 --> 12:59.430
AND HAD TO HAVE THEM
SURGICALLY REMOVED.

13:00.170 --> 13:01.781
YOU GUYS HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT YOU'RE GETTING INTO.

13:01.911 --> 13:04.305
-WE'RE GETTING INTO THREE
TO 500 DOLLARS A DAY.

13:05.001 --> 13:06.524
-EACH?
-EACH.

13:09.353 --> 13:10.659
-WELL THEY JUST FAXED
OVER YOUR ESTIMATE

13:10.790 --> 13:11.921
FROM THE AUTO SHOP.

13:12.052 --> 13:13.227
WHAT DID I SAY
IT WOULD COST?

13:13.357 --> 13:15.098
-1200 BUCKS,
WERE YOU RIGHT?

13:16.273 --> 13:17.361
-WHAT DO I
KNOW ABOUT CARS?

13:19.320 --> 13:20.756
-2000 BUCKS?

13:20.887 --> 13:22.236
FOR THAT PIECE OF JUNK?

13:22.366 --> 13:24.107
-I'LL CALL CAPTAIN
BOB, TELL HIM YOU'RE IN.

13:27.371 --> 13:28.546
-2000 BUCKS!

13:31.332 --> 13:32.812
OH MY GOD.

13:37.729 --> 13:40.428
-NOW, THE BEAUTY OF THIS
HOOKA RIG IS THAT YOU DON'T

13:40.558 --> 13:42.169
HAVE TO CARRY AROUND
THE HEAVY TANK YOU SEE.

13:42.299 --> 13:44.345
AS LONG AS I KEEP THE
GENERATOR GOING, YOU CAN WALK

13:44.475 --> 13:46.564
ALONG THE BOTTOM, SEE THE
URCHINS, AND JUST DROP EM.

13:46.695 --> 13:48.088
JUST TO YOUR
HEART'S CONTENT.

13:49.959 --> 13:51.656
-WHAT'S THE MATTER? AREN'T
YOU COMING WITH US?

13:51.787 --> 13:54.137
-I CAN'T DIVE TODAY, THIS
COLD'S GOT ME ALL STUFFED UP.

13:54.268 --> 13:55.573
IT WOULDN'T BE SAFE.

13:55.704 --> 13:56.748
-WE'RE GONNA MISS
YOU OUT THERE.

13:56.879 --> 13:58.272
-REMEMBER WHAT I TOLD YOU,

13:58.402 --> 13:59.969
WEAR YOUR GLOVES AND
USE THE URCHIN RAKE.

14:00.100 --> 14:01.231
-YOUR WHAT?

14:01.362 --> 14:02.798
-YOU KNOW, THE
TWEEZER THING.

14:02.929 --> 14:05.409
-HEY, LISTEN TO HER!
SHE KNOWS HER STUFF.

14:05.540 --> 14:07.063
-YEAH, MY DAD THOUGHT
HE COULD GET RICH

14:07.194 --> 14:08.978
DIVING FOR SEA
URCHINS IN HAWAII.

14:09.109 --> 14:10.110
-WE'LL BE FINE.

14:11.938 --> 14:12.982
-CODY: [FAKING
A SNEEZE] ACHOO!

14:14.636 --> 14:17.030
LET'S GO BOYS,
LET'S DO IT!

14:18.814 --> 14:21.295
-[GENTLE MUSIC]

15:52.908 --> 15:55.258
-LOOKING GOOD, DEB,
KEEP YOUR HEELS DOWN,

15:55.389 --> 15:57.260
YOU'RE LOCKING
YOUR ELBOWS AGAIN.

15:57.391 --> 15:58.435
LOOSEN UP A LITTLE.

16:02.048 --> 16:03.266
VERY NICE.

16:04.354 --> 16:05.442
THAT A GIRL.

16:05.573 --> 16:06.617
TAKE THIS LINE
ON THE RAIL.

16:10.230 --> 16:12.232
DON'T CHASE HIM INTO
IT, LET HIM JUST COME.

16:12.841 --> 16:14.147
VERY VERY NICE.

16:14.277 --> 16:15.278
VERY NICE.

16:15.409 --> 16:16.976
TAKE THE SECOND, PERFECT.

16:31.294 --> 16:32.426
NICE WORK.

16:38.649 --> 16:40.173
TAKE THIS NEXT
OVER HERE.

16:41.739 --> 16:43.350
GOOD GIRL,
THAT'S BETTER.

16:43.480 --> 16:44.960
MUCH BETTER.

16:52.359 --> 16:55.188
THAT'S SO MUCH BETTER THAN THE
LAST TIME YOU TOOK THAT JUMP.

16:55.318 --> 16:56.363
ALMOST PERFECT.

16:56.885 --> 16:58.147
KEEP YOUR HEELS DOWN.

16:58.278 --> 16:59.714
TAKE THIS VERTICAL.

17:03.587 --> 17:04.719
VERY VERY NICE.

17:04.848 --> 17:06.415
VERY NICE.

17:06.547 --> 17:08.201
OKAY, LET'S
CALL IT QUITS.

17:08.723 --> 17:10.637
WALK HIM OUT, GOOD JOB.

17:13.118 --> 17:14.294
-HEY.

17:17.123 --> 17:19.167
-MAN, I WISH I
COULD RIDE LIKE THAT.

17:19.777 --> 17:21.648
-WELL YOU CAN, IF YOU'RE
WILLING TO WORK HARD.

17:21.779 --> 17:23.825
IT JUST HAS TO BE SOMETHING
THAT YOU REALLY WANT.

17:25.914 --> 17:27.481
OKAY GUYS, THAT'S
IT FOR TODAY.

17:27.611 --> 17:29.396
WALK OUT YOUR HORSES AND
THEN GIVE 'EM TO ANTONIO.

17:29.526 --> 17:30.527
GOOD WORK.

17:32.181 --> 17:33.617
HOBIE'S A GREAT KID.

17:33.748 --> 17:35.010
YOU MUST BE VERY PROUD.

17:35.532 --> 17:36.620
-MORE THAN YOU KNOW.

17:36.751 --> 17:38.274
-IT'S A PLEASURE
TEACHING HIM.

17:38.405 --> 17:40.929
HE'S GOT SOME TALENT, A
GOOD SEAT, A LOT OF GUTS.

17:41.930 --> 17:43.279
-[MITCH LAUGHS]

17:43.410 --> 17:44.628
LOOKS LIKE HE'S ENJOYING
A LITTLE BIT MORE

17:44.759 --> 17:45.803
THAN JUST THE
RIDING, HUH?

17:47.370 --> 17:48.806
-LIKE FATHER, LIKE SON?

17:49.938 --> 17:50.852
-[HORSE WHINNIES]

17:50.982 --> 17:52.723
THERE HE IS, MAX.

17:52.854 --> 17:54.377
COME ON, I'LL
INTRODUCE YOU.

18:09.958 --> 18:11.568
MUCHAS GRACIAS, ANTONIO.

18:13.701 --> 18:15.181
MITCH, I WANT
YOU TO MEET MAX.

18:15.311 --> 18:16.225
-HEY, MAX.

18:16.356 --> 18:17.661
-[BOTH LAUGH]

18:17.792 --> 18:20.099
-I NAMED HIM AFTER
MY MOTTO IN LIFE.

18:20.795 --> 18:23.406
WHATEVER YOU DO,
YOU GOTTA LIVE LIFE,

18:23.537 --> 18:25.713
EXPERIENCE LIFE, AND YOU
GOTTA DO IT TO THE MAX.

18:26.888 --> 18:28.977
HE'S DEFINITELY LIVED UP TO
HIS NAME IN THE SHOW RING.

18:30.065 --> 18:33.242
HE'S A CHAMPION HUNTER, HE'S
WON EVERYTHING THERE IS TO WIN.

18:35.026 --> 18:36.463
-YOU SAID THAT
MAX WAS RECUPERATING

18:36.593 --> 18:37.638
FROM AN OPERATION, HUH?

18:38.291 --> 18:42.033
-YEAH, WELL, MAX IS
14 AND HE'S BEEN,

18:42.773 --> 18:44.558
WELL, JUMPING ALL HIS LIFE.

18:45.602 --> 18:47.474
HIS BACK LEGS ARE
GIVING HIM SOME TROUBLE.

18:48.431 --> 18:49.867
I GAVE HIM TIME OFF,

18:49.998 --> 18:50.868
IT JUST DIDN'T SEEM TO
MAKE ANY DIFFERENCE.

18:51.695 --> 18:54.089
ABOUT FOUR MONTHS AGO HE
WENT THROUGH HOCK SURGERY

18:54.829 --> 18:56.483
AND I'VE ONLY BEEN
ABLE TO RIDE HIM AGAIN

18:56.613 --> 18:57.745
THESE PAST FEW WEEKS.

19:01.749 --> 19:04.099
DOCTOR GRAY WILL BE
HERE LATER ON TODAY

19:04.708 --> 19:07.102
AND I'M KINDA NERVOUS HOW
MAX IS GONNA CHECK OUT.

19:08.538 --> 19:12.673
NO PUN INTENDED, BUT HIS
FUTURE'S KINDA RIDING ON THIS.

19:13.326 --> 19:15.328
-WELL, IF YOU
WANT, MAYBE I CAN

19:15.458 --> 19:17.852
TAKE YOUR MIND OFF THIS
FOR A COUPLE HOURS.

19:19.027 --> 19:20.811
WHAT DO YOU SAY WE HAVE A
LITTLE PICNIC ON THE BEACH?

19:20.942 --> 19:21.812
-YEAH?

19:21.943 --> 19:23.597
-THREE OF US, OF COURSE.

19:24.337 --> 19:26.034
-I THINK WE'D
LIKE THAT A LOT.

19:26.730 --> 19:27.818
-OKAY.

19:29.559 --> 19:34.869
-♪ YESTERDAY IS OVER LIKE
A SUDDEN SUMMER STORM ♪

19:36.044 --> 19:39.526
♪ TOMORROW IS A PROMISE

19:39.656 --> 19:42.485
WAITING TO BE BORN ♪

19:43.094 --> 19:45.923
♪ IN A WORLD THAT'S
ALWAYS CHANGING ♪

19:46.663 --> 19:49.275
♪ WHEN NOTHING
STAYS THE SAME ♪

19:50.058 --> 19:53.322
♪ IT'S HARD TO LEAVE
THE HURT BEHIND ♪

19:53.453 --> 19:56.151
♪ TAKE A CHANCE
ON LOVE AGAIN ♪

19:56.282 --> 19:59.459
♪ SO LET ME
HOLD YOU HERE ♪

20:00.024 --> 20:03.158
♪ AND FEEL
TIME DISAPPEAR ♪

20:04.942 --> 20:07.902
♪ NO NEED TO
BE AFRAID ♪

20:08.511 --> 20:11.210
♪ WE'RE GOING
ALL THE WAY ♪

20:11.949 --> 20:14.169
♪ BRAVE HEARTS
CAN MAKE IT ♪

20:14.300 --> 20:17.781
♪ TAKE IT TO THE MAX

20:19.000 --> 20:21.220
♪ HALFWAY TO HEAVEN

20:21.742 --> 20:24.614
♪ THERE'S NO
TURNING BACK ♪

20:25.963 --> 20:28.183
♪ STRONGER TOGETHER

20:28.749 --> 20:32.231
♪ YOU CAN
COUNT ON THAT ♪

20:33.057 --> 20:35.886
♪ IN LOVE FOREVER

20:36.670 --> 20:38.411
♪ TAKE IT TO THE MAX

20:38.541 --> 20:40.456
♪ TO THE MAX

20:44.634 --> 20:47.507
♪ LOVE COMES AND
GOES SO QUICKLY ♪

20:48.203 --> 20:50.988
♪ LIKE THE WAVES
UPON THE SHORE ♪

20:51.946 --> 20:55.123
♪ TOMORROW IS
A STRANGER ♪

20:55.254 --> 20:58.344
♪ KNOCKING AT MY DOOR

20:58.953 --> 21:02.173
♪ RELIEF ALL AROUND ME,

21:02.304 --> 21:05.133
THE WORLD CAN TAKE ITS TOLL ♪

21:05.916 --> 21:08.963
♪ I BLESS THE DAY
YOU FOUND ME ♪

21:09.093 --> 21:12.314
♪ ON LIFE'S LONG
AND LONELY ROAD ♪

21:12.445 --> 21:15.491
♪ WITH YOU HERE
IN MY ARMS ♪

21:15.622 --> 21:19.495
♪ I'M RIGHT
WHERE I BELONG ♪

21:20.322 --> 21:23.804
♪ SO TRUST IN
WHAT YOU FEEL ♪

21:23.934 --> 21:27.721
♪ BECAUSE THIS
LOVE IS REAL ♪

21:27.851 --> 21:30.158
♪ BRAVE HEARTS
CAN MAKE IT ♪

21:30.289 --> 21:34.249
♪ TAKE IT TO THE MAX

21:34.380 --> 21:36.991
♪ HALFWAY TO HEAVEN

21:37.121 --> 21:40.821
♪ THERE'S NO
TURNING BACK ♪

21:41.909 --> 21:47.523
♪ STRONGER TOGETHER,
YOU CAN COUNT ON THAT ♪

21:49.046 --> 21:51.527
♪ IN LOVE FOREVER

21:52.659 --> 21:54.138
♪ TAKE IT TO THE MAX

21:54.269 --> 21:56.010
♪ TO THE MAX

21:57.838 --> 22:03.104
♪ TAKE IT TO THE MAX 'CAUSE
THERE'S NO TURNING BACK ♪

22:07.413 --> 22:08.675
-YOU ALWAYS WORK
WITH HORSES?

22:09.458 --> 22:11.547
-YEAH, I WAS RIDING
BEFORE I COULD WALK.

22:16.291 --> 22:18.380
I CAN'T BELIEVE HOW
COMFORTABLE I FEEL WITH YOU.

22:19.816 --> 22:22.253
IT'S LIKE I'VE KNOWN YOU
FOR A VERY LONG TIME.

22:22.384 --> 22:23.777
-I KNOW WHAT YOU MEAN.

22:25.169 --> 22:26.867
I FEEL THE SAME WAY TOO.

22:28.956 --> 22:31.001
-YOU KNOW I SAW YOU
WATCHING ME RIDE MAX

22:31.132 --> 22:32.089
ON THE BEACH
ALL THOSE TIMES.

22:32.220 --> 22:33.221
-YOU DID NOT.

22:33.917 --> 22:35.005
OH MY GOD.

22:36.006 --> 22:38.574
-AND THEN THAT GOOD COP, BAD
COP ROUTINE WITH YOUR FRIEND

22:38.705 --> 22:39.923
AND THE INFAMOUS CITATION.

22:40.054 --> 22:40.881
-OH.

22:41.011 --> 22:42.839
-THAT PUT ME AWAY.

22:42.970 --> 22:45.712
AND WHEN YOU SIGNED HOBIE
UP FOR THOSE RIDING LESSONS.

22:46.495 --> 22:49.585
WELL, IT WAS SUCH AN
OLD FASHIONED APPROACH,

22:49.716 --> 22:50.978
IT REALLY TOUCHED ME.

22:54.634 --> 22:55.896
-CHEERS.
-CHEERS.

23:05.209 --> 23:06.646
-[PHONE RINGING]

23:07.386 --> 23:09.170
-MY ONLY EXTRAVAGANCE,

23:09.300 --> 23:11.433
JUST IN CASE SOMETHING
HAPPENS WITH A HORSE.

23:11.564 --> 23:14.001
-WHY AM I NOT SURPRISED?

23:16.090 --> 23:17.047
-JENNY WADE.

23:18.397 --> 23:19.223
OKAY.

23:20.094 --> 23:21.269
YES, I'LL BE THERE.

23:23.837 --> 23:25.621
THAT WAS DR. GRAY
CONFIRMING OUR APPOINTMENT

23:25.752 --> 23:27.928
THIS AFTERNOON FOR
MAX'S EVALUATION.

23:28.058 --> 23:30.365
-YOU REALLY LOVE
MAX A LOT DON'T YOU?

23:32.019 --> 23:34.238
-MAX'S MOM DIED
WHEN HE WAS BORN.

23:34.761 --> 23:36.806
I PULLED HIM OUT OF HER AND
BOTTLE FED HIM AS A COLT.

23:38.417 --> 23:40.680
I THINK HE GREW UP BELIEVING
THAT I WAS HIS MOTHER.

23:42.159 --> 23:43.857
I GUESS I TREATED
HIM AS MY CHILD.

23:43.987 --> 23:46.033
YOU ALWAYS WANT THE
BEST FOR YOUR CHILD.

23:48.644 --> 23:49.776
EVEN IF IT
BREAKS YOUR HEART.

23:51.778 --> 23:53.170
-WE THINK A LOT ALIKE.

23:53.301 --> 23:55.695
-YEAH, WE DO.

23:57.305 --> 23:59.612
-[SQUEALING TIRES]

24:00.439 --> 24:02.179
-[MOANING]

24:05.748 --> 24:07.315
-[SCREAMING]

24:15.062 --> 24:16.106
-CALL 911!

24:20.589 --> 24:22.809
-THERE'S BEEN AN ACCIDENT
AT NICHOLAS CANYON BEACH.

24:22.939 --> 24:24.375
THERE'S A CAR, IT'S
GONE OVER THE CLIFF

24:24.506 --> 24:25.289
AND IT'S IN THE WATER.

24:25.420 --> 24:26.639
WE NEED PARAMEDICS NOW.

24:27.291 --> 24:28.641
-WOMAN: HELP!

24:29.555 --> 24:31.165
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

24:31.295 --> 24:33.036
-[SCREAMING]

24:45.701 --> 24:50.053
[SCREAMING]

24:56.016 --> 24:58.540
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

26:03.126 --> 26:05.433
-[WOMAN SCREAMING]

26:21.362 --> 26:25.584
[SCREAMING]

26:27.847 --> 26:29.065
-DID YOU CALL 911?

26:29.196 --> 26:30.545
-I CALLED 911.
THEY'RE ON THEIR WAY.

26:31.981 --> 26:32.765
-IT'S TOO LATE.

26:32.895 --> 26:34.723
EASY, EASY.

26:34.854 --> 26:35.681
ALL RIGHT.

26:35.811 --> 26:37.204
-WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO?

26:37.334 --> 26:38.466
-WE'RE GONNA DELIVER
THIS BABY RIGHT NOW.

26:38.597 --> 26:40.120
GO GET THE
PICNIC BLANKET!

26:40.250 --> 26:41.382
-[SCREAMING]

26:41.512 --> 26:42.601
-PUT YOUR HEAD
DOWN. EASY.

26:42.731 --> 26:44.080
-OH GOD!

26:44.211 --> 26:45.212
-ALL RIGHT,
LISTEN TO ME.

26:46.082 --> 26:47.518
MY NAME IS MITCH, I'M
AN LA COUNTY LIFEGUARD.

26:47.649 --> 26:48.955
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

26:49.085 --> 26:50.696
-CYNTHIA.

26:50.826 --> 26:52.393
-ALL RIGHT, CYNTHIA.

26:52.523 --> 26:54.264
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE THIS BABY
RIGHT NOW ON THE BEACH.

26:54.395 --> 26:56.397
IT'S OKAY, WE DON'T HAVE TIME
TO GET YOU TO THE HOSPITAL.

26:56.527 --> 26:57.354
DON'T PUSH, DON'T PUSH.

26:57.485 --> 26:58.878
JUST REST. EASY.

26:59.008 --> 26:59.922
EASY, OKAY.

27:00.053 --> 27:01.532
NOW BLOW OUT, BLOW.

27:01.663 --> 27:03.360
I'VE DONE THIS BEFORE,
AND YOU BREATHE OKAY?

27:03.491 --> 27:05.014
BREATHE, BLOW.

27:05.145 --> 27:07.190
-OKAY, OKAY,
BREATHE. OKAY.

27:10.498 --> 27:12.152
-THAT'S IT!
BLOW! BLOW!

27:12.761 --> 27:14.110
OKAY. TAKE IT EASY.

27:14.241 --> 27:15.677
-IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.

27:17.026 --> 27:18.158
BREATHE.

27:18.288 --> 27:19.202
-IT'S COMING.

27:19.333 --> 27:20.551
IT'S COMING, PUSH!

27:20.682 --> 27:21.465
COME ON GIRL, PUSH!

27:21.596 --> 27:23.076
-[SCREAMING]

27:24.860 --> 27:25.948
-CYNTHIA, PUSH!

27:26.906 --> 27:28.647
COME ON CYNTHIA,
COME ON, GIRL, PUSH!

27:28.777 --> 27:29.648
PUSH!

27:30.474 --> 27:32.085
-I CAN'T, I CAN'T.

27:32.215 --> 27:33.390
-BREATHE, BREATHE.

27:33.521 --> 27:34.478
-PUSH! COME ON!

27:35.392 --> 27:36.176
-[CYNTHIA SCREAMING]

27:36.306 --> 27:37.394
IT'S COMING.

27:37.525 --> 27:38.744
-[SIRENS]

27:38.874 --> 27:39.962
-COME ON THAT'S IT.

27:43.052 --> 27:44.358
-MITCH: COME
ON, CYNTHIA!

27:45.968 --> 27:47.187
CYNTHIA, PUSH!

27:47.317 --> 27:48.275
COME ON, CYNTHIA!

27:49.798 --> 27:51.191
-GOOD GIRL.

27:51.321 --> 27:53.672
-COME ON, CYNTHIA.
COME ON, CYNTHIA. HEY!

27:53.802 --> 27:55.021
JENNY: GOOD GIRL!
MITCH: IT'S A BOY!

27:56.500 --> 27:58.677
-[BABY CRYING]

28:06.293 --> 28:07.120
-MITCH: THERE WE GO!

28:08.251 --> 28:10.689
-[JENNY CRYING]

28:17.391 --> 28:18.653
-[MITCH LAUGHS]

28:31.492 --> 28:32.798
-YOU NOTIFIED
THE COUNTY HUH?

28:39.108 --> 28:40.196
HEY.

28:40.327 --> 28:41.545
ALL DONE, THANKS
FOR WAITING.

28:42.808 --> 28:44.418
-WHAT AN INCREDIBLE DAY.

28:44.548 --> 28:46.550
IT STARTED OUT WITH A
FABULOUS RIDE ON THE BEACH,

28:46.681 --> 28:48.335
AND A LITTLE PICNIC
AND ALL OF A SUDDEN

28:48.465 --> 28:50.729
THERE'S A CAR IN THE WATER,
YOU'RE RESCUING THIS WOMAN

28:50.859 --> 28:52.469
AND WE DELIVER
HER BABY TOGETHER.

28:52.600 --> 28:54.733
AND IT'S NOT
EVEN, WHAT?

28:54.863 --> 28:56.169
IT'S NOT EVEN
TWO O'CLOCK!

28:56.735 --> 28:57.605
-YOU WANNA GO DANCING?

28:58.780 --> 29:01.348
-NO, I'M STILL REALLY
WORRIED ABOUT MAX.

29:01.478 --> 29:03.742
-HEY, WE HAD A VERY
LUCKY DAY, RIGHT?

29:04.612 --> 29:05.961
I'M SURE MAX IS
GONNA BE FINE.

29:06.745 --> 29:08.181
-EXCUSE ME.

29:08.311 --> 29:09.617
EXCUSE ME, I'M LOOKING
FOR MITCH BUCHANNON.

29:09.748 --> 29:11.097
-YEAH, YEAH
YOU FOUND HIM.

29:11.227 --> 29:13.577
-[LAUGHING] I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO THANK YOU!

29:14.796 --> 29:16.102
YOU SAVED MY
WIFE AND BABY!

29:16.232 --> 29:17.799
-OH!

29:17.930 --> 29:19.105
MY WIFE TRIED TO MAKE IT
TO THE HOSPITAL ON HER OWN

29:19.235 --> 29:20.454
WHEN SHE WENT
INTO LABOR BECAUSE

29:20.584 --> 29:22.021
SHE COULDN'T REACH
ME, YOU KNOW?

29:22.151 --> 29:23.370
AND THEN SHE LOST CONTROL
OF THE CAR BECAUSE

29:23.500 --> 29:24.414
THE INTENSE CONTRACTIONS
WERE SO BAD.

29:24.545 --> 29:25.589
I AM SO ANGRY WITH MYSELF.

29:25.720 --> 29:27.069
I SHOULD'VE BEEN
THERE FOR HER.

29:27.200 --> 29:28.505
YOU KNOW, MY CELL PHONE
BATTERY WENT DEAD.

29:28.636 --> 29:29.724
CAN YOU BELIEVE IT?

29:29.855 --> 29:31.073
HAS THAT EVER
HAPPENED TO YOU?

29:31.204 --> 29:32.248
I'LL NEVER FORGIVE
MYSELF BECAUSE

29:32.379 --> 29:33.162
I SHOULD'VE BEEN
THERE WITH HER.

29:33.293 --> 29:34.511
IT'S A BOY, IT'S A BOY!

29:34.642 --> 29:35.817
WELL YOU KNOW THAT,
YOU WERE THERE.

29:35.948 --> 29:36.775
HERE, HERE, HERE,
HAVE A CIGAR.

29:36.905 --> 29:37.776
OH, HERE, AND YOU TOO.

29:37.906 --> 29:39.386
-[ALL LAUGHING]

29:44.783 --> 29:45.784
-[GRUNTING]

29:47.002 --> 29:48.003
-CODY: YES SIR!

29:51.659 --> 29:53.139
-BOB: THAT'S
A FINE JOB.

29:55.619 --> 29:56.882
-SO HOW MUCH WE GOT
HERE CAPTAIN BOB?

29:57.012 --> 29:58.666
-OH, IT'S A REAL
NICE HAUL BOYS.

29:58.797 --> 30:00.668
I'D SAY YOU GOT A
COUPLE OF THOUSAND.

30:01.495 --> 30:04.280
OF COURSE, THAT'S
NOT COUNTING MY TAKE.

30:04.411 --> 30:05.891
-YEAH, BUT WE'RE STILL
NEGOTIATING, RIGHT?

30:06.021 --> 30:07.196
-DON'T THINK ABOUT IT.

30:07.327 --> 30:09.285
-STILL, NOT BAD
FOR A DAY'S WORK.

30:09.808 --> 30:10.896
-I'M JUST GLAD
YOU'RE OKAY.

30:12.114 --> 30:14.203
-MAN: HELP! HELP!

30:14.334 --> 30:15.422
HELP!

30:16.075 --> 30:17.467
-WHAT'S WRONG?

30:17.598 --> 30:19.600
-IT'S MY FRIEND, HE
WAS RIGHT BEHIND US

30:19.730 --> 30:20.819
BUT HE NEVER CAME UP.

30:20.949 --> 30:22.298
-WHERE'D YOU
LAST SEE HIM?

30:22.429 --> 30:24.518
-THE CAVE, WE WERE
EXPLORING THE CAVE,

30:24.648 --> 30:27.651
BUT OUR BOTTOM TIME'S
UP, WE REACHED OUR TABLE.

30:27.782 --> 30:29.436
-J.D., LET'S GO.

30:30.524 --> 30:33.919
-WE CAN'T DIVE, OUR
BOTTOM TIME IS UP TOO.

30:34.049 --> 30:35.442
-I'LL GO.

30:35.572 --> 30:36.747
-NO, WITH YOUR COLD
IT'S TOO DANGEROUS.

30:36.878 --> 30:37.966
-YOU WON'T BE
ABLE TO EQUALIZE.

30:38.097 --> 30:39.446
-YES I WILL,
I'LL BE FINE.

30:39.576 --> 30:41.100
WHO ELSE HERE'S GONNA GO?

30:41.709 --> 30:43.711
-OH, DON'T LOOK AT ME
FOLKS, I'M NO DIVER.

30:44.930 --> 30:46.453
-I'LL BE OKAY, JUST
HELP ME GEAR UP.

30:46.583 --> 30:47.846
-J.D., CALL FOR
BACKUP, MAN.

30:47.976 --> 30:48.847
-RADIO'S HERE.

30:52.676 --> 30:54.243
-YOU GOT IT?
-YEAH.

31:02.208 --> 31:03.557
-YOU KNOW, IT JUST
OCCURRED TO ME,

31:03.687 --> 31:05.037
MAYBE THEY SHOULD
NAME THAT BOY SANDY.

31:05.167 --> 31:06.734
-THAT'S APPROPRIATE.

31:06.865 --> 31:08.170
-HEY, HOBSTER, WHAT
YOU CARVING THERE?

31:08.301 --> 31:10.129
-UH NOTHING,
IT'S A SURPRISE.

31:10.825 --> 31:11.608
-CODE R.

31:11.739 --> 31:12.696
-WHAT'S A CODE R?

31:12.827 --> 31:13.828
-IT MEANS AN EMERGENCY.

31:16.135 --> 31:19.007
-[GENTLE MUSIC]

31:21.923 --> 31:23.185
-THERE'S NO OTHER
CHOICE, CODY,

31:23.316 --> 31:24.795
I'M A CERTIFIED
DIVER, REMEMBER?

31:25.753 --> 31:27.537
-ALL RIGHT, JUST BE
CAREFUL DOWN THERE OKAY?

31:27.668 --> 31:29.278
-IT'S NOT GONNA
BE A PROBLEM.

31:29.409 --> 31:30.279
-OKAY.

31:36.982 --> 31:38.244
-AIR'S ON.

31:39.723 --> 31:43.336
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

32:26.553 --> 32:28.729
-[SIRENS]

32:30.644 --> 32:31.993
-CODY: MITCH,
CHECK THE CAVE

32:32.124 --> 32:33.212
SOUTH OF OUR POSITION.

32:33.342 --> 32:34.822
-J.D.: LANI'S DOWN THERE.

32:35.388 --> 32:36.215
-WE'RE ON IT.

32:36.867 --> 32:37.694
YOU READY?

32:37.825 --> 32:38.695
-SUMMER: READY!

32:41.350 --> 32:45.746
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

32:55.625 --> 32:57.758
-[SCREAMING]

33:05.374 --> 33:09.074
-[OMINOUS MUSIC]

33:16.516 --> 33:18.474
-[SCREAMING]

33:51.681 --> 33:54.336
OH, OH MY GOD!

33:56.425 --> 33:58.166
I CAN'T HEAR ANYTHING!

33:58.297 --> 33:59.385
OH MY GOD!

34:01.387 --> 34:02.649
OH MY GOD!

34:04.390 --> 34:06.000
-SHE'S IN REAL BAD PAIN.
COME ON, GET HER UP.

34:06.131 --> 34:07.175
-I CAN'T HEAR ANYTHING!

34:07.741 --> 34:08.871
OH MY GOD!
-CODY: COME ON, COME ON!

34:09.003 --> 34:09.873
-ALL RIGHT, GRAB HER.

34:11.527 --> 34:13.007
-OW!

34:14.268 --> 34:15.792
OW! IT HURTS!

34:15.922 --> 34:17.446
-ALL RIGHT J.D., GET A
CHOPPER IN HERE RIGHT AWAY,

34:17.577 --> 34:18.926
TELL EM TO BRING A BASKET.

34:19.056 --> 34:20.058
WE NEED TO GET HER
TO THE HOSPITAL.

34:20.188 --> 34:21.581
-RIGHT AWAY.
-WHAT HAPPENED?

34:21.710 --> 34:22.495
-REVERSE PRESSURE.

34:22.625 --> 34:23.844
SHE DIDN'T EQUALIZE.

34:23.974 --> 34:25.454
SHE MAY HAVE
BLOWN HER EARDRUMS.

34:25.585 --> 34:26.847
LET'S GET A
BLANKET IN HERE.

34:26.976 --> 34:28.239
-CODY: IT'S
GONNA BE OKAY, WE

34:28.370 --> 34:29.197
HAVE A CHOPPER
ON THE WAY.

34:32.418 --> 34:35.333
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

34:41.427 --> 34:43.516
-OH MY GOD, I
CAN'T HEAR ANYTHING!

34:44.516 --> 34:45.822
PLEASE HELP ME!

34:48.608 --> 34:50.088
-MITCH: IT'S GONNA
BE ALL RIGHT, LANI.

34:50.217 --> 34:51.958
I CAN'T HEAR YOU,
I CAN'T HEAR YOU.

34:52.090 --> 34:55.005
PLEASE, PLEASE, HELP!

34:55.876 --> 34:57.399
OW, IT HURTS, PLEASE!

34:59.488 --> 35:01.142
OH MY GOD,
I'M SO SCARED.

35:01.273 --> 35:03.318
I'M SO SCARED.
CODY: IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.

35:03.449 --> 35:04.624
-OH PLEASE, CODY.

35:05.538 --> 35:06.800
CODY, WHAT'S GOING ON?

35:06.930 --> 35:08.149
PLEASE.

35:14.286 --> 35:15.635
-DO YOU KNOW WHERE
LANI MCKENZIE'S ROOM IS?

35:15.765 --> 35:16.549
-YEAH, SHE'S IN THE
FIRST DOOR ON THE RIGHT.

35:16.679 --> 35:17.550
-THANKS.

35:21.467 --> 35:22.337
-[CRASH]

35:22.468 --> 35:23.469
-CODY: I'M SORRY.

35:28.822 --> 35:29.823
SORRY.

35:40.138 --> 35:41.530
HEY.
-HI.

35:43.750 --> 35:46.274
IT FEELS SO WEIRD TO TALK
AND NOT HEAR MY VOICE.

35:58.243 --> 36:00.593
NO, NO IT'S
NOT YOUR FAULT.

36:01.594 --> 36:02.769
YOU CAN'T BLAME YOURSELF.

36:03.770 --> 36:07.252
I WANTED TO DIVE,
IT WAS MY DECISION.

36:11.908 --> 36:13.171
I'M JUST SCARED.

36:15.782 --> 36:17.523
I MEAN, EVERYTHING I LOVE,

36:18.828 --> 36:20.482
MUSIC AND LIFEGUARDING...

36:26.184 --> 36:29.230
-I'M SO SORRY, I NEVER
SHOULD HAVE LET YOU DIVE.

36:30.884 --> 36:32.059
IT'S ALL MY FAULT.

36:34.192 --> 36:35.193
I'M SORRY.

36:36.411 --> 36:38.196
-[SOMBER MUSIC]

36:53.428 --> 36:54.777
-STILL NO ANSWER?

36:54.908 --> 36:56.344
-NO, NO.

36:56.475 --> 36:57.998
-DAD, WHY DON'T YOU
JUST GO OVER THERE

36:58.128 --> 36:59.956
AND SEE IF JENNY'S OKAY?

37:00.087 --> 37:01.784
-WELL I WENT ON MY FIRST DATE
WITH HER YESTERDAY, YOU KNOW?

37:01.915 --> 37:04.004
I JUST CAN'T SHOW
UP ON HER DOORSTEP

37:04.134 --> 37:05.919
AT SEVEN O'CLOCK IN THE
MORNING UNANNOUNCED.

37:06.049 --> 37:07.790
-YEAH, WELL THE WAY I
SEE IT, IF TWO PEOPLE

37:07.921 --> 37:10.271
BRING A BABY INTO THIS WORLD
TOGETHER, ON THE BEACH,

37:10.402 --> 37:12.752
UNANNOUNCED SO TO SPEAK,
THEY SHOULD BE ABLE

37:12.882 --> 37:14.057
TO WAVE ALL THE
FIRST DATE CRAP.

37:14.884 --> 37:17.060
-YOU KNOW, I ALWAYS THOUGHT
YOU'D GROW UP SOME DAY

37:17.191 --> 37:18.627
AND GIVE ME SOME ADVICE.

37:18.758 --> 37:20.238
BUT, I NEVER THOUGHT
THAT I WOULD TAKE IT.

37:22.675 --> 37:23.502
-HEY, DAD?

37:24.546 --> 37:25.895
IS LANI GONNA
BE ALL RIGHT?

37:26.026 --> 37:27.897
-UH, I TALKED TO THE
DOCTOR AND HE SAID

37:28.028 --> 37:30.726
THAT SHE WAS RESTING
COMFORTABLY BUT, THEY DON'T KNOW

37:30.857 --> 37:33.251
WHETHER HER HEARING LOSS IS
GONNA BE TEMPORARY OR PERMANENT.

37:34.164 --> 37:35.165
SEE YA.

37:35.296 --> 37:37.255
-[SOFT MUSIC]

37:59.189 --> 38:00.190
-MITCH: HEY!

38:01.366 --> 38:02.410
SEEN JENNY THIS MORNING?

38:02.541 --> 38:03.585
-SHE'S OVER IN MAX'S STALL.

38:03.716 --> 38:04.499
-MITCH: THANKS.

38:04.630 --> 38:07.763
-[GENTLE MUSIC]

38:29.437 --> 38:30.438
-MITCH: HEY.

38:31.613 --> 38:32.484
'MORNING.

38:33.136 --> 38:34.921
COME HERE.
LOOK AT YOU.

38:35.878 --> 38:38.011
LOOK, I'M SORRY TO
COME OVER SO EARLY,

38:38.141 --> 38:39.621
IT'S JUST THAT I
CALLED LAST NIGHT

38:39.752 --> 38:41.406
AND WHEN YOU DIDN'T ANSWER
THE PHONE I GOT WORRIED.

38:41.536 --> 38:44.234
-I KNOW, I SPENT THE
NIGHT HERE IN MAX'S STALL.

38:45.671 --> 38:49.152
-OH, I ALMOST FORGOT,

38:50.415 --> 38:51.938
HOBIE ASKED ME
TO GIVE YOU THIS.

38:52.068 --> 38:53.461
-OH.

38:54.593 --> 38:57.073
-HE TOLD ME TO TELL YOU THAT
AS MUCH AS HE LIKES HORSES,

38:57.204 --> 38:58.814
HE'D RATHER...

38:58.945 --> 39:01.469
-I KNOW, HE'D RATHER BE
CARVING THEM THAN RIDING THEM.

39:03.602 --> 39:04.472
IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

39:06.431 --> 39:08.563
-SORRY I COULDN'T BE HERE
FOR YOU AND MAX LAST NIGHT.

39:08.694 --> 39:10.260
-NO, THAT'S OKAY.

39:10.391 --> 39:12.175
I CALLED HEADQUARTERS
WHEN YOU DIDN'T SHOW UP,

39:12.306 --> 39:13.438
I TOTALLY UNDERSTAND.

39:16.179 --> 39:17.267
JUST WALK.

39:21.750 --> 39:22.621
OH.

39:22.751 --> 39:23.578
-IS HE ALL RIGHT?

39:24.274 --> 39:25.232
-THIS TIME.

39:26.364 --> 39:28.191
I DON'T KNOW HOW
HE'S GONNA STAND IT,

39:28.322 --> 39:29.932
BEING COOPED UP IN
THERE LIKE THAT.

39:33.196 --> 39:36.722
-DON'T YOU WORRY MAX,
WE'RE GONNA FIND A SOLUTION.

39:37.853 --> 39:39.464
-I WISH HE UNDERSTOOD
THAT I'M JUST TRYING

39:39.594 --> 39:41.117
TO DO WHAT'S BEST
FOR HIM, YOU KNOW?

39:46.775 --> 39:48.211
I'M SO SORRY TO
HEAR ABOUT LANI.

39:49.212 --> 39:52.085
I HATE TO DWELL ON MY OWN
PROBLEMS WHEN SHE'S, WELL...

39:52.955 --> 39:54.348
I JUST PRAY SHE'S
GONNA BE OKAY.

39:56.132 --> 39:58.396
-JENNY, I DON'T THINK TWO
PEOPLE HAVE BEEN THROUGH MORE

39:58.526 --> 40:01.747
IN THE FIRST 24 HOURS OF
KNOWING EACH OTHER THAN WE HAVE.

40:02.791 --> 40:03.792
-IT'S NOT OVER YET.

40:04.837 --> 40:06.273
-DOCTOR GRAY CHECK MAX OUT?

40:07.753 --> 40:10.190
-DOCTOR GRAY SAID THAT
MAX CAN'T JUMP ANYMORE.

40:11.017 --> 40:13.585
HE CAN ONLY RUN LIGHTLY
AND NOT WORK TOO HARD.

40:14.803 --> 40:16.631
-WELL, THAT'S NOT
TOTALLY BAD NEWS.

40:16.762 --> 40:21.244
I MEAN, HE SEEMS REALLY
HEALTHY, HE'S PAIN FREE.

40:21.375 --> 40:22.637
I MEAN, YOU CAN
SPOIL HIM TO DEATH

40:22.768 --> 40:25.771
AND HE CERTAINLY
SEEMS HAPPY.

40:26.902 --> 40:29.209
-WELL, HE WON'T
BE IF HE HAS TO

40:29.339 --> 40:31.124
SPEND THE REST OF HIS
LIFE IN THAT STALL.

40:31.864 --> 40:33.126
I JUST CAN'T DO
THAT TO HIM.

40:33.996 --> 40:35.911
BREAK MY HEART TO SEE
HIM COOPED UP LIKE THAT.

40:37.609 --> 40:41.526
DOCTOR GRAY SAYS THAT MAX
NEEDS TO BE ABLE TO MOVE AROUND

40:41.656 --> 40:43.615
IN A BIG SOFT
GRASSY PASTURE.

40:43.745 --> 40:45.530
I COULD NEVER AFFORD
A PLACE LIKE THAT.

40:46.139 --> 40:48.533
-WHICH IS EXACTLY WHY I WANTED
TO SEE YOU TODAY ABOUT MAX.

40:49.447 --> 40:50.665
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

40:50.796 --> 40:51.753
-JENNY, I JUST
CAME FROM VISITING

40:51.884 --> 40:53.581
A FRIEND OF MINE IN MALIBU.

40:53.712 --> 40:55.801
LAST YEAR WE SAVED HER HORSES
FROM GOING TO SLAUGHTER.

40:55.931 --> 40:57.803
WELL, SHE WANTS TO
RETURN THE FAVOR,

40:58.412 --> 40:59.282
ESPECIALLY FOR MAX.

41:00.109 --> 41:01.807
-I STILL DON'T UNDERSTAND.

41:01.937 --> 41:05.071
-SHE LIVES ON A BEAUTIFUL
RANCH IN MALIBU WITH HER HORSES.

41:05.201 --> 41:07.856
LAKES, GRASSY
PASTURES, EVERYTHING.

41:07.987 --> 41:09.945
SHE SAID MAX CAN STAY THERE
AS LONG AS HE NEEDS TO

41:10.076 --> 41:11.556
TO GET BETTER.

41:11.686 --> 41:13.427
-MITCH, THAT'S STILL
GONNA COST A FORTUNE.

41:13.558 --> 41:15.255
-HOW DOES FREE SOUND?

41:16.430 --> 41:18.171
-FREE?
-FREE.

41:20.216 --> 41:21.696
-I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO SAY.

41:21.827 --> 41:22.958
I DON'T KNOW HOW TO THANK
YOU, OR YOUR FRIEND.

41:23.089 --> 41:26.135
-YOU CAN THANK
US BY ACCEPTING.

41:26.266 --> 41:27.659
-I DO!

41:27.789 --> 41:31.445
-[TRIUMPHANT MUSIC]

41:44.806 --> 41:46.634
-[END THEME MUSIC]
